<P><A NAME=Anchor0></A><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>WHATS NEW?</B></FONT></P>

<P>This area gives brief details of changes to the web site, where
and when to help update your information about the club.</P>

<P><B>Date</B></P>

<P>98/09/20 - Revision of homepage and small design changes</P>

<P>98/10/13 - Revision of homepage (changes to schedule and
contacts), added <A HREF="hakone.htm">Hakone information</A></P>

<P>98/10/19 - Revision of homepage (changes to schedule), added
<A HREF="yatsu.htm">Yatsugatake information</A> and <A HREF="north_alps1.htm">North
Alps</A> link. Also, the proposed <A HREF="guidelines.htm">TWMC
guidelines</A> are for everyone to view and <A HREF="mailto:john.payne@kyowa.co.jp">comment</A>
on.</P>

<P>98/10/20 - Addition of links to <A HREF="oze1.htm">Oze</A>,
<A HREF="fuji1.htm">Fuji trip 1</A>, <A HREF="fuji2.htm">Fuji trip
2</A>, <A HREF="kamakura.htm">Kamakura</A>, <A HREF="north_alps1.htm">North
Alps</A>, and <A HREF="south_alps1.htm">South Alps</A>. Most of these
links have links to pictures or include some pictures with addition
of descriptions of the walks and some slanderous accusations from
Victor...</P>

<P>98/10/21 - Buying or loooking for gear? Well, before you buy, take
a look at the updated web pages on <A HREF="page3.htm">hiking
advice</A> where there are links to choosing / help on <A HREF="boots.htm">walking
boots</A> , <A HREF="rucksack.htm">rucksacks</A> , <A HREF="sleepbag.htm">sleeping
bags and mats</A> , and <A HREF="tent.htm">tents (help on buying,
variety, maintenance, pitching, and care of them)</A>.</P>

<P><B>98/11/05</B> - Want to know where we are going walking in the
future, or where we have been? <A HREF="map_page.htm">Then try the
new MAP PAGE which allows some degree of interaction in searching
Japan</A> (all maps (C) <A HREF="http://www.mapple.co.jp/">Shobunsha
Publications, Inc. from "Road Atlas Japan"</A>. The TWMC would like
to thank <A HREF="http://www.mapple.co.jp/">Shobunsha</A> for their
kindness in allowing these images to be used.). If you have a car or
want to find out where places are in Japan, the "Road Atlas Japan" is
the BEST map to buy - most place names in Kanji and Romaji (so useful
for nihonji and gaikokujin!) and always up-to-date. We recommend you
to buy it (about 2500 yen).</P>

<P>

<HR>

</P>

<P><A NAME=Anchor1></A><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>TWMC - very brief
introduction</B></FONT></P>

<P>This is a new club - the <FONT COLOR="#0033FF"><B>Tsukuba Walking
and Mountaineering Club</B></FONT>, formed in May 1998. We decided to
form the club as many people (Japanese and <I>gaikokujin</I>)
expressed the wish to go walking in Japan, including us, and so we
decided to do something about it and organise walks for everyone
where we would like to visit as many wonderful places as possible in
Japan. We try and do walks for everyone and all standards of walking.
Join us and see. You couldn`t meet a more friendly bunch of people...
We are also known as the Tsukuba Walking and Onsen Club from time to
time as we do try to find an onsen whenever we can!</P>

<P>

